-- Dufry, Novartis, Partners Group, Sonova: Swiss Equity Preview
-- B y   G i l e s   B r o o m
-- 2010-11-16T07:37:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-16/dufry-novartis-partners-group-sonova-may-move-swiss-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in Zurich. Stock
symbols are in parentheses after company names. Share prices are
from the last close.  The Swiss Market Index of the biggest and most actively
traded companies advanced 0.9 percent to 6,562.15. The broader
Swiss Performance Index climbed 0.8 percent to 5,835.85.  Dufry Group  (DUFN SW): The owner of duty-free shops
reported net earnings to equity holders of 83.5 million francs
for the first nine months of 2010 compared with 28.3 million the
previous year period. The shares rose 3.8 percent to 119.40
francs.  New Value AG  (NEWN SW): The clean tech and healthcare
investment company reported a loss of 1.99 million francs for
the six months ending Sept. 30 compared with a profit of 10.17
million for the prior year period. The shares fell 1.1 percent
to 13.40 francs.  Novartis AG  (NOVN VX): The Basel, Switzerland-based drug
maker said it has not ruled out operating  Alcon Inc . with its
existing 77 percent stake as minority investors seek an improved
offer for the outstanding shares, the Financial Times reported.
The shares gained 1.5 percent to 55.50 francs.  Partners Group Holding AG  (PGHN SW): The Swiss money
manager said it has opened an office in Seoul. The shares
increased 0.3 percent to 177.00 francs.  Sonova Holding AG  (SOON VX): The hearing-aid maker reported
operating profit before amortization of 204 million francs for
the first six months of its 2010-11 financial year compared with
193.7 million francs in the prior year period. Sales increased
17 percent to 831.5 million francs. The shares surged 1.9
percent to 121.80 francs.  Temenos Group AG  (TEMN SW): The software provider announced
it is calling for an early redemption of 132.25 million francs
of 1.5 percent convertible bonds due 2013. Bondholders can
either convert their bonds into shares by Dec. 17 or expect
repayment on this date. The shares added 2 percent to 34.05
francs.  Tornos SA  (TOHN SW): Europe’s biggest maker of lathes for
the watch industry reported third-quarter orders worth 50.4
million francs. The shares advanced 0.9 percent to 11.40 francs.  UBS AG  (UBSN VX): Switzerland’s largest bank holds an
investor day in London where the Zurich-based company will
reconfirm its medium-term targets to be achieved within a three
to five year period. UBS said 15-40 billion francs of the bank’s
invested assets may be affected by potential changes to European
double taxation treaties with Switzerland. The shares climbed
0.3 percent to 16.94 francs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Giles Broom  in Zurich at 
 gbroom@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
